16/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski launched an official visit to Turkey on Tuesday (15 April).
He will meet with his Turkish counterpart, Vecdi Gonul, to discuss bilateral co-operation, particularly broader technical support to the Macedonian Army.
Also Tuesday, the Macedonian government adopted a plan to contribute to the international post-war coalition for reconstruction of Iraq.
The draft will be submitted for parliamentary approval next week.
Meanwhile, a German delegation met with Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski in Skopje Tuesday, to discuss military co-operation and the EU rapid reaction force in Macedonia.
Later the delegation met with Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva, to discuss efforts to fight organised crime and corruption.
In other news, amid mounting pressure, President Boris Trajkovski has decided to go before parliament next week to explain his recent decision to pardon two senior officials involved in wire-tapping scandal.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik, Vest - 16/04/03;
MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 15/04/03)
